  "description": "Bucharest, Romania's capital, is a city of striking contrasts where Belle Époque architecture meets communist-era buildings. Known as 'Little Paris' in the early 20th century, the city features elegant French-style buildings alongside the massive Palace of the Parliament, the world's second-largest administrative building. The historic Old Town offers charming cobblestone streets and vibrant nightlife, while the Village Museum showcases traditional Romanian rural architecture. Bucharest's unique character comes from its blend of Western European influences, Orthodox Christian heritage, and communist-era legacy, creating a fascinating urban landscape that tells the story of Romania's complex history.",
